The paper deals with techniques for enhancing the performance of MIMO systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The use of Channel State Information (CSI) and coding also suggests the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of beamforming techniques and multiple antennas points towards the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
